cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "Trapetum: fused codebook-quantization kernels and a pure-Rust LLM runtime"
authors:
  - family-names: "Mimouni"
    given-names: "A."
repository-code: "https://github.com/Tomahawk888/trapetum"
license: CC-BY-4.0
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-25"
keywords:
  - CUDA
  - GPU kernels
  - LLM inference
  - weight quantization
  - codebook quantization
abstract: >
  A kernel-level study of fused dequantization plus matmul for codebook
  (non-uniform / k-means) weight quantization of LLM linear layers. The lookup is
  folded into the GEMV/GEMM so the dequantized weight matrix is never materialized.
  Throughput is benchmarked against cuBLAS fp16 on synthetic data with fixed seed.
  This repository measures kernel performance only; it does not evaluate model
  accuracy.
